chHWType.name: chHWType
chHWType.description: Indicates type of enclosure in which the FIBRONICS SNMP agent operates.

chNumberOfSlots.name: chNumberOfSlots
chNumberOfSlots.description: Number of manageable slots in the chassis. In FIBRONICS implementation it describes the number of manageable slots in the chassis (not all slots should be occuppied).

chNumberOfEthernetBuses.name: chNumberOfEthernetBuses
chNumberOfEthernetBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal Ethernet buses provided by the box.

chNumberOfTRBuses.name: chNumberOfTRBuses
chNumberOfTRBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal Token Ring buses provided by the box.

chNumberOfFDDIBuses.name: chNumberOfFDDIBuses
chNumberOfFDDIBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal FDDI buses provided by the box.

chNumberOfLocalTalkBuses.name: chNumberOfLocalTalkBuses
chNumberOfLocalTalkBuses.description: Indicates the number of internal Local Talk buses provided by the box.

chReset.name: chReset
chReset.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON is interpreted as a reset command for the whole chassis. It initiates a complete reinitialisation of the chassis and of all the devices incorporated inside the chassis.

chFullConfig.name: chFullConfig
chFullConfig.description: Full configuration message retrieved by FIBRONICS management stations at periodic interrogation times. Coded in compact internal FIBRONICS application format.

chGenAgTable.name: chGenAgTable
chGenAgTable.description: Table of configuration attributes common to all SNMP agents in FIBRONICS hubs.

chGenAgEntry.name: chGenAgEntry
chGenAgEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing configuration attributes for a single agent.

chGenAgId.name: chGenAgId
chGenAgId.description: Agent index for identifying the agent.Takes the value of the slot number where the agent card is inserted. For box agents the value of chGenAgId is chNumberOfSlots+1.

chGenAgMgmtIfType.name: chGenAgMgmtIfType
chGenAgMgmtIfType.description: This attribute describes one of the interfaces of agents existing on FIBRONICS modules and their type. Value 'none' defines the lack of an interface recognized by the management console. Any other value defines an interface whose type is recognized by the management console and may be used as a management channel.

chGenAgAddr.name: chGenAgAddr
chGenAgAddr.description: This attribute defines an unique address by which the agent may be addressed by the management console. The address format should be consistent with the type defined by chGenAgMgmtIfType.

chGenAgSpecificOID.name: chGenAgSpecificOID
chGenAgSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

chFbrAgTable.name: chFbrAgTable
chFbrAgTable.description: Table of configuration attributes of FIBRONICS SNMP box agents in FIBRONICS hubs.

chFbrAgEntry.name: chFbrAgEntry
chFbrAgEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing configuration attributes for a single agent.

chFbrAgId.name: chFbrAgId
chFbrAgId.description: Agent index for identifying the agent. Identical to the index in chGenAgTable for the described agent.

chFbrAgSLIPAddress.name: chFbrAgSLIPAddress
chFbrAgSLIPAddress.description: IP address of the SLIP channel of the agent

chFbrAgSWVersion.name: chFbrAgSWVersion
chFbrAgSWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent software version.

chFbrAgKernelVersion.name: chFbrAgKernelVersion
chFbrAgKernelVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent operating system (kernel) version.

chFbrAgCoprocSWVersion.name: chFbrAgCoprocSWVersion
chFbrAgCoprocSWVersion.description: ASCII string describing the software version of the agent's coprocessor.

chFbrAgSWFault.name: chFbrAgSWFault
chFbrAgSWFault.description: System fault emitted by agent software. It covers faults detected by the agent operating system and drivers. EnterpriseSpecific traps mechanism is used for transfering these traps to the management system.

chFbrAgMgmtBusSelection.name: chFbrAgMgmtBusSelection
chFbrAgMgmtBusSelection.description: Attribute describing the number of the bus on which management data are reported.

chFbrAgCoprocCommStatus.name: chFbrAgCoprocCommStatus
chFbrAgCoprocCommStatus.description: Attribute describing the status of the communication between the agent and its coprocessor.

chFbrAgCommDebugMode.name: chFbrAgCommDebugMode
chFbrAgCommDebugMode.description: Attribute describing the agent mode in which communication problem traps are sent to managers (value 'on') or are not sent to managers (value 'off').

chFbrAgConfigChangeTraps.name: chFbrAgConfigChangeTraps
chFbrAgConfigChangeTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Configuration Change traps to the manager.

chFbrAgFaultTraps.name: chFbrAgFaultTraps
chFbrAgFaultTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Fault traps to the manager.

chFbrAgTrafficThreshTraps.name: chFbrAgTrafficThreshTraps
chFbrAgTrafficThreshTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Traffic Threshold traps to the manager.

chFbrAgGroupEnrollDeenrollTraps.name: chFbrAgGroupEnrollDeenrollTraps
chFbrAgGroupEnrollDeenrollTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Group Enrollment and Group Deenrollment traps to the manager.

chFbrAgSoftFaultTraps.name: chFbrAgSoftFaultTraps
chFbrAgSoftFaultTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Software Fault traps to the manager.

chFbrAgHubEnrollTraps.name: chFbrAgHubEnrollTraps
chFbrAgHubEnrollTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends periodic Hub Enrollment traps to the manager.

chFbrAgTempThreshTraps.name: chFbrAgTempThreshTraps
chFbrAgTempThreshTraps.description: The value of this attributes determines whether or not the agent sends Temperature Threshold traps to the manager.

chFbrAgSpecificOID.name: chFbrAgSpecificOID
chFbrAgSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

chFbrAgLastAddrConfig.name: chFbrAgLastAddrConfig
chFbrAgLastAddrConfig.description: Configuration attribute describing the last physical address detected at each port. Coded in internal FIBRONICS application format.

chFbrAgSecAddrConfig.name: chFbrAgSecAddrConfig
chFbrAgSecAddrConfig.description: Configuration attribute describing the configuration of the secure addresses. Coded in internal FIBRONICS application format.

chFbrAgSoftwareStatus.name: chFbrAgSoftwareStatus
chFbrAgSoftwareStatus.description: Describes configuration of the firmware on this agent. unLoadable(1) - is returned by agents which do not support the Software Download feature; loaded(2) - is returned by agents with loaded software; downLoading(3) - when the attribute is set to this value by manager, it triggers the Software Download procedure. When procedure finished, agent software will restablish value loaded(2).

chFbrAgConfigurationSymbol.name: chFbrAgConfigurationSymbol
chFbrAgConfigurationSymbol.description: Defines the Configuration Symbol attached to any hardware module manufactured by FIBRONICS. One single character A..Z defines the CS version. For older modules which did not support this option on SNMP character '*' will be returned.

chFbrAgIntTemp.name: chFbrAgIntTemp
chFbrAgIntTemp.description: Internal temperature measured by the temperature sensor placed on the agent card. Expressed in Celsius degrees.

chFbrAgBootVersion.name: chFbrAgBootVersion
chFbrAgBootVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the agent boot software version.

chFbrAgSensorFault.name: chFbrAgSensorFault
chFbrAgSensorFault.description: A code of a sensor fault discovered by the agent.

chFbrAgSensorFaultTraps.name: chFbrAgSensorFaultTraps
chFbrAgSensorFaultTraps.description: This attribute enables/disables generation of the sensor fault trap.

chFbrAgInterProcFault.name: chFbrAgInterProcFault
chFbrAgInterProcFault.description: A code of intercommunication fault between Main - Master processors.

chFbrAgInterProcFaultTraps.name: chFbrAgInterProcFaultTraps
chFbrAgInterProcFaultTraps.description: This attribute enables/disables generation of the intercommunication fault trap.

chFbrAgPermMngrEntry.name: chFbrAgPermMngrEntry
chFbrAgPermMngrEntry.description: An entry in the permanent managers table.

chFbrAgPermMngrId.name: chFbrAgPermMngrId
chFbrAgPermMngrId.description: Index in the permanent managers table. It ranges from 1 to chFbrAgMaxNmbOfMngrs

chFbrAgPermMngrAddr.name: chFbrAgPermMngrAddr
chFbrAgPermMngrAddr.description: IP address of a permanent manager.

chFbrAgRmtNetEntry.name: chFbrAgRmtNetEntry
chFbrAgRmtNetEntry.description: Entry in the remote networks table.

chFbrAgRmtNetId.name: chFbrAgRmtNetId
chFbrAgRmtNetId.description: Index of a remote network. It ranges from 1 to chFbrAgMaxNmbOfNets.

chFbrAgRmtNetAddr.name: chFbrAgRmtNetAddr
chFbrAgRmtNetAddr.description: Address of a remote network. The host portion is always 0.

chFbrAgRmtNetMask.name: chFbrAgRmtNetMask
chFbrAgRmtNetMask.description: Subnet mask for the remote network.

chFbrAgDateTime.name: chFbrAgDateTime
chFbrAgDateTime.description: Current date and time for NMA-TR. The format is YYMMDDhhmmssw, where w - day of the week e.g., 1=Mon, 2=Tue,..., 7=Sun.

chFbrAgReset.name: chFbrAgReset
chFbrAgReset.description: This attribute enables the user to reset the agent.

chMgrTrapRepStatus.name: chMgrTrapRepStatus
chMgrTrapRepStatus.description: Value 'on' indicates that SNMP agent should send SNMP traps (traffic ex- cluded) to the manager.

chMgrContPerfRep.name: chMgrContPerfRep
chMgrContPerfRep.description: Value 'on' indicates that the SNMP agent should send traffic SNMP traps to the manager.

chMgrMngmtState.name: chMgrMngmtState
chMgrMngmtState.description: Attribute to be set by manager in order to instruct the agent to enter into a management session with the console. Setting this value to 'on' has the effect of performing an 'I am your manager' action upon the agent.

chMgrPollInterval.name: chMgrPollInterval
chMgrPollInterval.description: The attribute defines an interval during which the agent is waiting for the manager's requests. Default value 5 minutes.

chHWPSUTable.name: chHWPSUTable
chHWPSUTable.description: Table of configuration attributes for Power Supply Units. This table can be retrieved only from agents equipped with adequate hardware.

chHWPSUEntry.name: chHWPSUEntry
chHWPSUEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing configuration attributes for a single Power Supply Unit.

chHWPSUId.name: chHWPSUId
chHWPSUId.description: PSU index for identifying the PSU.

chHWPSUActivityStatus.name: chHWPSUActivityStatus
chHWPSUActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of the PSU in what concerns supplying power to the chassis. NotActive - indicates a disabled or defective PSU which cannot supply power to the chassis. Dormant - indicates a functional PSU which is installed for backup purposes and can at any moment supply power to the devices in the chassis. Active - indicates that the PSU supplies power to the chassis.

chHWPSULocation.name: chHWPSULocation
chHWPSULocation.description: Describes the location (internal or external) of the PSU.

chHWPSUVoltage.name: chHWPSUVoltage
chHWPSUVoltage.description: Indicates voltage of PSU expressed in miliVolts.

chHWIntTempWarning.name: chHWIntTempWarning
chHWIntTempWarning.description: Fault condition indicating that the temperature measured by one of the sensors internal to the box exceeded chHWIntTempThresh.

chHWIntTempThresh.name: chHWIntTempThresh
chHWIntTempThresh.description: Internal enclosure temperature threshold value, expressed in degrees Celsius. When exceeded, a trap is sent to the management console.

chHWPeakIntTemp.name: chHWPeakIntTemp
chHWPeakIntTemp.description: Maximum internal temperature inside the chassis. It is the maximum of the temperature values detected by different temperature sensors inside the box.

chSlotLastChange.name: chSlotLastChange
chSlotLastChange.description: This attribute contains the value of sysUpTime at the time any of the modules in the hub was enrolled/deenrolled.

genGroupTable.name: genGroupTable
genGroupTable.description: Table of configuration attributes for managed FIBRONICS modules. Includes configuration data which are independent of the specific functionality of the module.

genGroupEntry.name: genGroupEntry
genGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single group.

genGroupId.name: genGroupId
genGroupId.description: Index which identifies the group inside the chassis for which this entry contains information. Equals the number of the slot by which the group is accessed. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

genGroupSWVersion.name: genGroupSWVersion
genGroupSWVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the group software version.

genGroupKernelVersion.name: genGroupKernelVersion
genGroupKernelVersion.description: ASCII string for description and display of the group kernel version.

genGroupType.name: genGroupType
genGroupType.description: Attribute describing the type of FIBRONICS Ethernet group.

genGroupDescr.name: genGroupDescr
genGroupDescr.description: Descriptor of the group in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

genGroupNumberOfPorts.name: genGroupNumberOfPorts
genGroupNumberOfPorts.description: Number of ports in group. It is assumed that on each group the ports are assigned unique numbers in the range from 1 to genGroupNumberOfPorts. They correspond to the number of ports on the module (FRU)

genGroupNumberOfIntPorts.name: genGroupNumberOfIntPorts
genGroupNumberOfIntPorts.description: Number of internal ports (ports connected to the chassis buses) on the module.

genGroupReset.name: genGroupReset
genGroupReset.description: Setting the value of this attribute to 'on' is interpreted as a software RESET command. Sensor software is reinitialized and according to the sensor specifications, partial or total reset of the module hardware may be performed.

genGroupAutoMan.name: genGroupAutoMan
genGroupAutoMan.description: This attribute reflects the status of the Auto/Manual switch which defines the working mode of FIBRONICS sensors. In the MANUAL mode no set operations may be performed on attributes related to the sensor. The sensor works according to configuration switches set by hardware and transmits all configuration information to the agent. In the AUTO mode, hardware switches are overridden by set commands.

genGroupFullConfig.name: genGroupFullConfig
genGroupFullConfig.description: Attribute describing the full configuration of a group in internal FIBRONICS application format.

genGroupRedun12.name: genGroupRedun12
genGroupRedun12.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between synchronous external ports 1 and 2 on a FIBRONICS module.

genGroupRedun34.name: genGroupRedun34
genGroupRedun34.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between synchronous external ports 3 and 4 on a FIBRONICS module.

genGroupRedun13_14.name: genGroupRedun13_14
genGroupRedun13_14.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between synchronous external ports 13 and 14 on a FIBRONICS module.

genGroupStandAloneMode.name: genGroupStandAloneMode
genGroupStandAloneMode.description: Value ON of this attribute indicates the sensor's operation Stand Alone mode . Internal ports are disabled and the card functions in a local star configuration toward its external ports.

genGroupInterProcCommStatus.name: genGroupInterProcCommStatus
genGroupInterProcCommStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the communication between the microprocessor of the sensor and the microprocessor of the agent on cards with embedded agents.

genGroupCommStatus.name: genGroupCommStatus
genGroupCommStatus.description: This attribute describes the communication status of the group with the SNMP Agent as detected and reported by the agent.

genGroupHWStatus.name: genGroupHWStatus
genGroupHWStatus.description: This attribute describes the status of the group hardware as detected by the sensors software.

genGroupSupplyVoltageFault.name: genGroupSupplyVoltageFault
genGroupSupplyVoltageFault.description: A value 'on' of this attribute informs of a 'voltage supply out-of-range' error condition on sensor equipped with hardware which checks this condition.

genGroupIntTemp.name: genGroupIntTemp
genGroupIntTemp.description: Internal temperature of the enclosure as measured by the specific module instance.

genGroupSpecificOID.name: genGroupSpecificOID
genGroupSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

genGroupConfigurationSymbol.name: genGroupConfigurationSymbol
genGroupConfigurationSymbol.description: Defines the Configuration Symbol attached to any hardware module manufactured by FIBRONICS. One single character A..Z defines the CS version. For older modules which did not support this option on SNMP character '*' will be returned.

genGroupLastChange.name: genGroupLastChange
genGroupLastChange.description: This attribute contains the value of sysUpTime at the time any change pertaining to the specified group occurred.

genPortTable.name: genPortTable
genPortTable.description: Table of configuration attributes for managed FIBRONICS ports. Includes configuration data which are independent of the specific functionality of the port.

genPortEntry.name: genPortEntry
genPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single port.

genPortGroupId.name: genPortGroupId
genPortGroupId.description: Index which identifies the group inside the chassis for which this entry contains information. Equals the number of the slot by which the group containing the port is accessed. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

genPortId.name: genPortId
genPortId.description: Index which identifies the port inside the group for which this entry contains information. It generally corresponds with the number by which the port is identified and is marked on the module. This value is never greater than genGroupNumberOfPorts of the group to which the port belongs.

genPortFunctionality.name: genPortFunctionality
genPortFunctionality.description: Describes the functionality of the port according to international standards.

genPortType.name: genPortType
genPortType.description: Attribute describing the type of FIBRONICS port.

genPortDescr.name: genPortDescr
genPortDescr.description: Descriptor of the port in ASCII (readable) format, mainly for use with generic management applications.

genPortActivityStatus.name: genPortActivityStatus
genPortActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of ports that may be part of a redundancy scheme. NotActive - indicates a disabled port which cannot transmit or receive packets even if included in a redundancy scheme. Dormant - indicates an enabled port which does not transmit or receive packets, but because it is included in a redundancy scheme, it may at any moment become responsible packet transmission and reception. Active - indicates that the port transmits and receives packets, serving as the main path in the redundant configuration.

genPortSecurityPolicy.name: genPortSecurityPolicy
genPortSecurityPolicy.description: Security policy (Trap Only or Trap and Close) assigned to this port. The information is coded in internal FIBRONICS format.

genPortSecureAddresses.name: genPortSecureAddresses
genPortSecureAddresses.description: This attribute defines the security information (physical addresses) relevant for the entry. Coded in internal format, cryptographic methods may be used for privacy purposes.

genPortIntPortConnection.name: genPortIntPortConnection
genPortIntPortConnection.description: The value of this attribute defines the internal port to which the port is connected. A value 0 of this attribute would indicate no internal port connection (stand-alone mode). Any other positive value equals the number of the internal port.

genPortAdminStatus.name: genPortAdminStatus
genPortAdminStatus.description: A disabled port neither transmits nor receives. The port must be explici- tenly enabled to restore operation. For token ring ports, this attribute is read-only.

genPortSpecificOID.name: genPortSpecificOID
genPortSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

genIntPortTable.name: genIntPortTable
genIntPortTable.description: Table of configuration attributes of FIBRONICS internal ports. Internal ports are physical and/or logical entities which transfer information and connect FIBRONICS modules to the internal networks (buses).

genIntPortEntry.name: genIntPortEntry
genIntPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single port.

genIntPortGroupId.name: genIntPortGroupId
genIntPortGroupId.description: Index which identifies the group inside the chassis for which this entry contains information. Equals the number of the slot by which the group containing the internal port is accessed. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

genIntPortId.name: genIntPortId
genIntPortId.description: Index which identifies the port inside the group for which this entry contains information. This value is never greater than genGroupNumberOfIntPorts of the group to which the port belongs.

genIntPortAdminStatus.name: genIntPortAdminStatus
genIntPortAdminStatus.description: Defines the capability of the internal port to transmit or receive data. A disabled internal port neither transmits or receives. The port must be explicitly enabled to restore operation.

genIntPortActivityStatus.name: genIntPortActivityStatus
genIntPortActivityStatus.description: This attribute defines the status of internal ports that may be part of a redundancy scheme. NotActive - indicates a disabled port which cannot transmit or receive packets even if included in a redundancy scheme. Dormant - indicates an enabled port which does not transmit or receive packets, but because it is included in a redundancy scheme, it may at any moment become responsible for packet transmission and reception. Active - indicates that the port transmits and receives packets, serving as the main path in the redundant configuration.

genIntPortBusConnNumber.name: genIntPortBusConnNumber
genIntPortBusConnNumber.description: The value of this attribute defines the bus to which the internal port is connected. The value '0' indicates that the port is disconnected from the bus.

genIntPortBusConnType.name: genIntPortBusConnType
genIntPortBusConnType.description: The value of this attribute defines the type of the bus to which the internal port is connected.

genIntPortSpecificOID.name: genIntPortSpecificOID
genIntPortSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

genIntPortMonitorMode.name: genIntPortMonitorMode
genIntPortMonitorMode.description: This attribute enables to monitor a specified bus (RMON).

softRedundancyTable.name: softRedundancyTable
softRedundancyTable.description: Table of attributes which define software redundancy links defined by means of the FIBRONICS chassis SNMP agents.

softRedundancyEntry.name: softRedundancyEntry
softRedundancyEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single software redundancy link.

softRedundancyId.name: softRedundancyId
softRedundancyId.description: Index which identifies the software redundancy link which for which the current entry provides information.

softRedundancyName.name: softRedundancyName
softRedundancyName.description: Logical name of the software redundancy link

softRedundancyGroupId1.name: softRedundancyGroupId1
softRedundancyGroupId1.description: ID of the group to which the main port on the software redundancy link belongs. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

softRedundancyPortId1.name: softRedundancyPortId1
softRedundancyPortId1.description: ID of the main port on the software redundancy link.

softRedundancyGroupId2.name: softRedundancyGroupId2
softRedundancyGroupId2.description: ID of the group to which the secondary port on the software redundancy link belongs. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

softRedundancyPortId2.name: softRedundancyPortId2
softRedundancyPortId2.description: ID of the secondary port on the software redundancy link.

softRedundancyStatus.name: softRedundancyStatus
softRedundancyStatus.description: Status of the entry in the softRedundancy Table: valid(1) indicates that row is busy with meaningful values; createRequest(2) will be set by manager when creating a new row; underCreation(3) indicates that agent accepts create command and performs it; invalid(4) indicates that no meaningful values are present in the row. Managers set this value in order to transmit a 'Delete row' command to agent.

ethAgTable.name: ethAgTable
ethAgTable.description: Table of attributes which define configuration characteristics for FIBRONICS chassis SNMP agents which use Ethernet as in-band management protocol.

ethAgEntry.name: ethAgEntry
ethAgEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single Ethernet agent.

ethAgId.name: ethAgId
ethAgId.description: Index which identifies the Ethernet agent for which the current entry provides information.

ethAgPerfBusSelection.name: ethAgPerfBusSelection
ethAgPerfBusSelection.description: Attribute describing the bus attached to the performance data collection hardware on those FIBRONICS agent hardware implementations which support configuration management on multi-Ethernet bus enclosures, but performan- ce data collection on a single bus.

ethGroupTable.name: ethGroupTable
ethGroupTable.description: Table of attributes which define configuration characteristics for FIBRONICS Ethernet modules.

ethGroupEntry.name: ethGroupEntry
ethGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing data about a single Ethernet module (group).

ethGroupId.name: ethGroupId
ethGroupId.description: Index which identifies the group inside the chassis for which this entry contains information. Equals the number of the slot by which the group is accessed. This value is never greater than chNumberOfSlots.

ethGroupFIFO.name: ethGroupFIFO
ethGroupFIFO.description: Value ON of this attribute describes an internal FIFO error sensed by the internal hardware mechanism of a FIBRONICS repeater.

ethGroup10BTPlus.name: ethGroup10BTPlus
ethGroup10BTPlus.description: Value ON of this attribute defines activation of the 10BaseTPlus mode - a FIBRONICS extension of the 10BaseT standard.

ethGroupIntPortsRedundancy.name: ethGroupIntPortsRedundancy
ethGroupIntPortsRedundancy.description: Value ON of this attribute defines a redundancy (backup) relationship between internal ports 1 and 2 on a FIBRONICS module.

ethGroupBackboneMode.name: ethGroupBackboneMode
ethGroupBackboneMode.description: Value On of this attribute defines Backbone Mode of a sensor. Internal ports are enabled and the information path goes straightly from external port to internal bus, via corresponding internal port.

ethGroupFOIRLPlusMode.name: ethGroupFOIRLPlusMode
ethGroupFOIRLPlusMode.description: Value On of this attribute defines FOIRL of a sensor. When this attribute has value ON, FOIRL Plus mode is enabled, while value OFF indicates stan- dard FOIRL mode.

ethGroupWrongPortSelection.name: ethGroupWrongPortSelection
ethGroupWrongPortSelection.description: A value ON of this attribute warns of incorrect selection of enabled ports on sensors which impose restrictions on this configura- tion (e.g. integrated local bridges.)

ethGroupBackupBus.name: ethGroupBackupBus
ethGroupBackupBus.description: Defines the common secondary bus for Ethernet groups with bus redundancy defined at port level.

ethGroupSingleBusMode.name: ethGroupSingleBusMode
ethGroupSingleBusMode.description: Value 'on of this attribute defines bus-star mode for cards supporting this type of configuration.

ethGroupSpecificOID.name: ethGroupSpecificOID
ethGroupSpecificOID.description: This attribute provides the OID of another group containing additional more specific information regarding this instance.

ethGroupMasterClock.name: ethGroupMasterClock
ethGroupMasterClock.description: This attribute pertains to the SH-E16 chassis and defines the hub in the stack that generates the clock.

ethGroupIdleTrx.name: ethGroupIdleTrx
ethGroupIdleTrx.description: This attribute is relevant to the LE-120Q/SQ modules and when set to 'off' after port disable terminates also light propagation (for redundancy tests).

ethGroupMJLPStatus.name: ethGroupMJLPStatus
ethGroupMJLPStatus.description: This attribute defines the MJLP error status on the group level.

ethPortGroupId.name: ethPortGroupId
ethPortGroupId.description: Id of the group to which the port belongs.

ethPortId.name: ethPortId
ethPortId.description: Unique Id of the port in the ethPortTable.

ethPortFunctionalStatus.name: ethPortFunctionalStatus
ethPortFunctionalStatus.description: The value of this attribute reflects the functional status of FIBRONICS synchronous ports. Note that it is not mandatory that all ports support all the enumerated states. Here is the minimal set possible states: OK - fully functional port, transmitting and receiving packets. RLD - receive link down condition on the port. TLD - transmit link down condition on the port. LocalJabber - fault condition indicating that the port emitted jabber. RemoteJabber - fault condition indicating that remote jabber was sensed at the port. IllSeq - Fault condition indicating an illegal synchronization sequence at the port. ShortCircuit - short-circuit fault condition detected at the port. PartitionOrLocalJabber - RemoteFaultOrLockLoss -

ethPortManPart.name: ethPortManPart
ethPortManPart.description: Setting the value of this attribute to ON activates the manual partition mechanism at the port level. Setting the value of this attribute to OFF cancels the partition mechanism. The segment may reconnect after the reception of 32 packets. Attribute vaild for repeater modules from the LE-10 family.

ethPortJabber.name: ethPortJabber
ethPortJabber.description: Value ON of this attribute reflects jabber transmitted to the port by the hardware of a FIBRONICS repeater or transceiver, as a result of collisions detected on the port. Valid for all modules in the LE-10 and LE-15 families.

ethPortNoAUILoop.name: ethPortNoAUILoop
ethPortNoAUILoop.description: Value ON of this attribute indicates that a No AUI Loop fault condition was detected on an AUI repeater port. Valid for LE-10C family of modu- les.

ethPortMJLP.name: ethPortMJLP
ethPortMJLP.description: Value ON of this attribute describes an internal MJLP (MAU Jabber Lockup Protection) error sensed by the internal hardware mechanism of a FIBRONICS repeater. Valid for LE140XTF.

ethPortFIFO.name: ethPortFIFO
ethPortFIFO.description: Value ON of this attribute describes an internal FIFO error sensed by the internal hardware mechanism of a FIBRONICS repeater. Valid for LE140XTF.

ethPortAutoPartitionState.name: ethPortAutoPartitionState
ethPortAutoPartitionState.description: The AutoPart condition indicates that the port is currently partitioned by the auto-partition protection mechanism.

ethPortSQETest.name: ethPortSQETest
ethPortSQETest.description: Settable attribute which allows activation of SQE test for FIBRONICS integrated transceivers.

ethPortLastSourceAddr.name: ethPortLastSourceAddr
ethPortLastSourceAddr.description: Ethernet source address of the last readable frame received by this port.

ethPortUserStatus.name: ethPortUserStatus
